<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "2B">
<servcat sctnbr = "02" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A2206013" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Front Suspension Frame, Stabilizer Bar and Bushing Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A2206012">Front Suspension Frame and Stabilizer Bar Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
If the front suspension frame is not stably supported on a transmission jack or other supporting equipment during its removal and installation, the frame could drop and cause personal injury.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Make sure that the weight of the front suspension frame is supported at the frame’s center and that the frame is well balanced on the support.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Touching a hot exhaust system component will cause a burn.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Do not perform any service work on the exhaust system until the exhaust system is cool.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A2206013001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect steering lower shaft from pinion shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle and remove front wheels. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove engine undercover.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove muffler mounting from front suspension frame. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect stabilizer joint from stabilizer bar.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect tie-rod end from steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove suspension arm. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove suspension frame members (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B220004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.864mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "156"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Support engine assembly using chain hoist (1) or engine crane.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B220008.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "81.124mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "213"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove engine rear mounting bolts. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406013"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Support front suspension frame (2) using transmission jack (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220028.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "61.934mm" ver = "01" gw = "237" gh = "159"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove suspension frame mounting No.1 bolt (1) and No.2 bolt (2), then lower transmission jack to remove suspension frame (3) together with stabilizer bar and steering gear case from vehicle body.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B220009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.315mm" ver = "01" gw = "165" gh = "146"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering gear case assembly from front suspension frame. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove stabilizer mounting bracket (1), stabilizer bar bushing (2) and stabilizer bar (3) from front suspension frame (4).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A220003.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.253mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "106"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A2206013002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A2206014">Front Suspension Frame Check</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A2206015">Front Stabilizer Bar, Bushing and Joint Check</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install stabilizer bar (1), stabilizer bar bushing (2) and stabilizer mounting brackets (3) to front suspension frame as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to face up painted surface (5) on stabilizer bar (1).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to match stabilizer bar bushing end (2) with ring (4) of stabilizer bar.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten stabilizer mounting bracket bolts to specified torque in numerical order of “1” and “2” as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B009">
<t-part>
Stabilizer mounting bracket bolt*
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
30
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
3.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
22.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A220004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "87.099mm" ver = "02" gw = "213" gh = "230"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.634in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "0.634in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[f]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Forward
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
6.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Slit
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering gear case assembly to front suspension frame. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Put front suspension frame (2) on transmission jack (1) and raise jack.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220032.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "61.934mm" ver = "01" gw = "237" gh = "159"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Align right and left bosses (1) of front suspension frame with holes (2) in vehicle body.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220033.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.824mm" ver = "01" gw = "229" gh = "145"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new suspension frame mounting No.1 bolt (1) and No.2 bolt (2) and tighten them to specified torques.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B010">
<t-part>
Suspension frame mounting No.1 bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
95
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
9.7
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
70.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T2B011">
<t-part>
Suspension frame mounting No.2 bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
95
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
9.7
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
70.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B220010.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.315mm" ver = "01" gw = "173" gh = "146"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install suspension frame member (1) as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Install suspension frame member then tighten suspension frame member No.2 bolt (2).
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B012">
<t-part>
Suspension frame member No.2 bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
55
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
40.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Tighten suspension frame member No.1 bolt (3) and suspension frame member nut (4).
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2B013">
<t-part>
Suspension frame member No.1 bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
55
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
40.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T2B014">
<t-part>
Suspension frame member nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
c
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
55
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
40.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B220007.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.864mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "156"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower transmission jack.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install engine rear mounting bolts to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406013"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove chain hoist from engine assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install suspension arms to front suspension frame, then finger tighten new suspension arm front bushing bolt and suspension arm rear bushing bolt temporarily by hand. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect suspension arm joint to steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect tie-rod end to steering knuckle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect stabilizer joint to stabilizer bar. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install muffler mounting to front suspension frame. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install engine undercover. 
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install front wheels and tighten wheel nuts to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect steering lower shaft to pinion shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower hoist and bounce vehicle up and down several times to stabilize suspension. And then, tighten suspension arm front bolt and rear bolt to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check front wheel alignment. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A2206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
